item.title: About
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
View Resume

Ever since I was young I have always been fascinated with technology. I think that my curiosity started when I was two years old and began using the computer. The countless hours that I spent playing games on an old desktop computer turned into my passion to understand more about them. As I grew up, I became more interested in learning how they work and the endless possibilities of what they, and technology, can do.

I pursued a degree in Computer Science and graduated with a bachelorâ€™s degree, but I quickly realized that an education is a lifelong adventure and learning more about what a computer can do is something I am committed to doing, which is what has led me to learning how to become a web developer.

My blog is about technology. It is a place about discovery, invention, and the pure amazement that technology brings to the world. It is a place where I will share personal stories along with news that is technology related.

If you share my passion of technology and are as fascinated as I am about its innovations, please follow my blog. Together we can learn how it is forever changing the world that we live in.  

I hope you enjoy.

Garrison

item.title: Best Choice for Social Distancing
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
Ten months ago, we never imagined that we would be living in a world that is so cut off from society, but that is todayâ€™s new reality. Nowadays the world is learning how to live socially distant. Most of us are listening to the experts who say that standing six feet apart and wearing a mask is what will keep us the safest, and when we cannot do that, we should stay home. By remaining at home people are realizing more and more throughout this Covid-19 quarantine just how valuable technology really is. It is evident through the many social connections that technology is bringing to every corner of the globe.

The role that technology is currently playing in our lives is quite amazing! There was a time not too long ago when critics would say that we spend too much time in front of our screens, but now that time in front of those screens is what is keeping us sane. Without the use of bits and bytes we would all be going a little bit more stir crazy than we already are. The screens that we hold in our hands or the ones that stare back at us in our laps or at our desks are becoming the most important comfort apparatus that we have. Technology is helping parents to be teachers, employees to work from home, and curious people to learn new skills. Not to mention how much that the use of technology is entertaining us with movies and games, satisfying our shopping pleasures, and helping to feed our hungry stomachs along with contactless delivery. It is also helping supply chains tackle the enormous task of managing their goods.

Without the use of technology, the burden to get through this challenging time would be rather heavy. It is unimaginable to think of life without technology, especially currently when many of us are looking for endless ways to keep us content and happy. Like it or not, technology is what is helping society to stay socially distant and that is a good thing.

https://percentotech.com/7-technological-trends-being-used-to-tackle-the-challenges-of-the-coronavirus-pandemic/

item.title: I Can See Through You
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
One of the latest designs in technology is LGâ€™s development of an innovative high-tech transparent 55-inch TV. With their new LG Transparent OLED signage, the product will allow viewers to see not only what is on the screen, but also the images, people, or events that are behind it. It is amazing what the viewers experience will be like.

Being able to install the new LG Transparent OLED signage in various ways and places will allow it to blend into open places flawlessly. And itâ€™s tempered protective glass will add to its durability. The downside of this new display is that some consumers will find this product a bit too futuristic, but the realization of what can be seen may actually take your breath away.

It may take a while for the average consumer to get used to a product like this. Having a display in front of you and still being able to see what is behind you may get confusing on what you are actually looking at. Seeing your children and or pets and also what is on the screen at the same time may be difficult to focus on. Pricing will be another downside, although LG has not put a price on their product yet, and most likely a luxury that most of us will not be able to afford.

The advancement in televisions in the past decade is something that we all can appreciate, and this latest LG product could take it to the next level. I find it an exciting product for the future and one that I would love to own someday when I am wealthy enough to be able to.

item.title: Digital or Paper
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
Today consumers have a choice as to which type of book that prefer to use for their reading, the growing in popularity eBook or the decreasingly outdated paper book. The type of book that you choose most often just comes down to your preference. I personally like to use both. An eBook is convenient at times for some of my classes and other times a paper book is much more helpful for both reading and comprehending the material. Both types of books have their advantages and disadvantages.

Do you really need to turn a physical page?

An eBook can be available to you in a matter of seconds with quick downloads. And since eBooks are portable they can be easily read on any device that you own. E books are often less expensive than a paper book. Prices may vary depending on the book that you choose, but usually eBooks cost 50% less than their counterparts, and without having to pay for shipping costs. Grabbing your latest device and reading in the dark is something that cannot be done with a paper book. How cool is that? And customizing the font the size to fit your needs is another plus. Another feature of an eBook that I like is that they are searchable. You can easily search for a term, a quote, or a part of a story. And no one can complain how they are saving the environment.

But with every advantage comes disadvantages. I think one of the biggest disadvantages of an eBook is that you cannot achieve the same satisfaction of holding an actual paper book in your hands. To a lot of people that makes a huge difference. Another disadvantage is that downloads can occur illegally be being hacked or copied which hurts authors. Minor disadvantages with digital eBooks are that they do not last forever on your device and it will require your device to be charged.

The debate can go on forever. In the end all that matters is that you are reading and stimulating your mind!

https://www.toptenreviews.com/the-pros-and-cons-of-ebooks

item.title: Sales Are Booming!!
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
Computers change the way we work, live, play, and think. And if you were one of the lucky ones who purchased a PC in 2020 you added the economic PC sales growth that occurred!

The growing demand for digital devices has never been higher. Students, parents, employees, and everyday consumers around the globe have been more connected than ever and it shows. Sales of PCâ€™s worldwide have soared in 2020 with a total of PC units sold rising to 275 million. That is a 4.8 increase in one year. All thanks largely due to the pandemic.  In the fourth quarter of 2020, US sales alone rose 20.6%. Sales have not been this robust since 2010.

The top selling PC companies each have seen dramatic increases in PC sales. These brands are a favorite choice of millions of consumers that sell not only PCs, but also monitors, keyboards, and software. Lenovo continued to lead the global PC market in 2020 with 24.7% of the sales. That adds up to a whooping 21.5 million units! HP made up 19.8% of the market with 15.6 million units sold.  And Dell came in third in the PC market share with selling 13.1 units and making up 16.6% of the market.

Computers are the tools for students, parents, employees, engineers, scientists, and everyday consumers. Keeping up with your workload demand requires a top-notch PC. Your children need PCâ€™s to keep pace with their remote learning schoolwork. And the fun-loving gamer needs a device that can provide fast graphics.

If sales continue to be strong in the first quarter 2021, now might be the perfect to time to invest in a new PC. And you might even get a great sale price!

item.title: The Other Blue Lights You Have to Worry About
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
My sister works as a technician who makes glasses, and she keeps telling our family that we need to worry about the damaging blue light rays. When I first heard her mention this, I had no idea what she was talking about. I thought eyeglasses were made to correct our vision, not to help in preventing harmful rays. I thought that was more of what sunglasses were for.

She explained that blue light blocking glasses are specifically designed to filter out the harmful blue-violet light rays that are commonly emitted from our digital screens. She continued explaining about the harmful rays and it all began to make sense.

Since we spend the majority of our day staring at a screen our eyes are working harder than ever, so it does seem possible that there should be some concern. Eye problems that can occur are tired eyes, disrupted sleep, eyestrain, dry or irritated eyes, headaches, and even blurred vision. We need to pay attention to what our eyes are telling us.

Sure, avoiding screens would be an easy fix, but come on, no one can do that. Screens are our source for communication, social interaction, news, entertainment, and work and school. For those reasons and more we must find ways to protect our eyes from the negative effects of the digital screens. Prescription and non-prescription blue light blocking lenses are available to protect our eyes from exposure while working, gaming, or just being online.

Maybe investing in a pair wouldnâ€™t be such a bad idea after all.

item.title: Knock Knock
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
Whoâ€™s there?

I am.

A spy at your door.

The latest trend in doorbells is a video one and it has exploded onto the market. Gone are the days when a visitor or a delivery person would knock at your door or ring your doorbell without the person inside having a clue as to who it is. Todayâ€™s latest doorbells not only alert you that someone is at your door, but they also serve as a home security surveillance device.

The video doorbell device has a modern design and is easy to install. The doorbell is positioned outside your door in place of your existing doorbell. Most models come equipped with a microphone and speaker allowing you to not only see who is at your door, but also to carry on a conversation with that person.

The video doorbell connects to an app on your Apple or Android device which then alerts you of activity at your door. It allows you to view and record the activity, in real time, with high-definition color quality. Its capability also allows you to see the activity in the street in front of your house or possibly even across the street to your neighborâ€™s house. Its night vision technology lets you to see what is happening at night as well.

Another huge function of a video doorbell is that it aids in neighborhood security. With the instant notification and video recording, it helps to fight crime in your area. By receiving an alert of an unwanted thief or intruder, you can quickly contact the police. Once they are notified you have the capability to send clear high-definition footage of the perpetrator and his/her actions to the authorities. Some video doorbell brands such as Ring, allow you to connect to the Ring community of other users in the area to help fight crime in your neighborhood or nearby.

It is a great product to invest in for peace of mind without paying the high price of bulky security cameras.

https://www.safety.com/how-do-doorbell-cameras-work/

item.title: Smartwatches vs Fitness Trackers
item.dc:creator: glee9308
item.content:encoded:
You have finally decided that now is the time to get in shape. Your next step is deciding which type of device to purchase to track your progress, should you buy a smart watch or a fitness tracker? Is there even a difference? Turns out the answer is yes and no.

Both devices have the ability to monitor your fitness goals by tracking your steps and your heart rate, and both have a similar appearance.

A smartwatch is basically a miniature phone on your wrist. It is an all-in-one device with a touch screen display, but it does a lot more than just tell time.  It not only tracks your fitness, but it also allows you to read your messages, check notifications, view incoming calls, and so much more.

Some smartwatches even go a step further. They can monitor your sleep, your stress, and your heart. They come with GPS technology and app features that can play music, provide you with coaching to improve your speed and endurance, provide you with a daily workout, and they even have the capability to make payments for you. These are just a few of the additional things that they can do.

Fitness trackers are slimmer in design. They are thin, lightweight bands that track your steps, heart rate, and distance. They come with built in GPS. Fitness trackers are usually less expensive than a smartwatch because they are simple and only track your activity. Because of their simplistic design and function, they come with a longer battery life.

So, if you want a fitness device that does the basics, tracks your activity, and you are not that interested in high end features, and you want to spend the least amount of money as possible, then go with a fitness tracker. It will do the job for you. On the other hand, if you are looking for something that does more than just track your fitness, and you like to have features right at your fingertips without much effort, and you do not mind spending the extra money, then a smartwatch is the one for you.

Either choice is a great motivation tool to help you achieve your fitness goals!

https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/smartwatch-vs-fitness-tracker/
